          {
            "title": "Intro",
            "id": 71870,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Aprendamos un nuevo concepto que explica cómo las variables hacen un seguimiento de cosas como agregar o quitar dólares de una billetera.</p><webview version=\"2\" visible-if=\"always\" content=\"&lt;!doctype html&gt;&#xA;&lt;html&gt;&#xA; &lt;head&gt;&#xA;  &lt;style&gt;&#xA;   button {&#xA;    background-color: darkBlue;&#xA;    /* Green */&#xA;    border: none;&#xA;    border-radius: 8px;&#xA;    color: white;&#xA;    text-align: center;&#xA;    text-decoration: none;&#xA;    display: inline-block;&#xA;    font-size: 14px;&#xA;    padding: 6px 12px;&#xA;    margin: 0 12px 0 0;&#xA;   }&#xA;  &lt;/style&gt;&#xA; &lt;/head&gt;&#xA; &lt;body&gt;&#xA;  &lt;h1&gt;Wallet: &lt;strong&gt;$&lt;span id=&quot;amount&quot;&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;  &lt;button onclick=&quot;add()&quot;&gt;Add $1&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;  &lt;button onclick=&quot;remove()&quot;&gt;Remove $1&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;  &lt;script&gt;&#xA;   let wallet = 15;&#xA;   let amountCounter = document.getElementById('amount');&#xA;   &#xA;   function add() {&#xA;    wallet += 1;&#xA;    amountCounter.innerHTML = wallet;&#xA;   }&#xA;   &#xA;   function remove() {&#xA;    wallet -= 1;&#xA;    amountCounter.innerHTML = wallet;&#xA;   }&#xA;  &lt;/script&gt;&#xA; &lt;/body&gt;&#xA;&lt;/html&gt;\" /></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Assigning a value",
            "id": 71871,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Cuando creamos una variable, le <strong>asignamos</strong> un valor, como asignar <code>3</code> a <code>wallet</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" wallet = \" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(wallet);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"13\" endIndex=\"14\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"===\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"3\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>=</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Self-assigning a value",
            "id": 71872,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p><strong>Autoasignación</strong> es cuando asignamos a una variable su propio valor. Por ejemplo, podemos asignar a <code>wallet</code> su valor <code>3</code> con <code>wallet = wallet</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" wallet = \" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"wallet = wallet;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(wallet);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"16\" endIndex=\"22\" /><option startIndex=\"23\" endIndex=\"24\" /><option startIndex=\"25\" endIndex=\"31\" /><option startIndex=\"31\" endIndex=\"32\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"3\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>wallet</code> seguido de <code>=</code> y luego <code>wallet</code>, <code>;</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Incrementing numbers",
            "id": 71873,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Ya que podemos autoasignar variables, podemos aumentar o disminuir variables establecidas en números. Intenta aumentar <code>wallet</code> con <code>wallet = wallet + 1</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" wallet = \" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"wallet = wallet + \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(wallet);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"25\" endIndex=\"35\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"3 + 1\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"4\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>wallet + 1</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Why self-assigning matters",
            "id": 71881,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Las variables de autoasignación nos permiten rastrear datos que cambian con el tiempo. Por ejemplo, un usuario podría agregar <code>2</code> dólares a una billetera y luego retirar <code>1</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" wallet = \" /><text value=\"3\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"wallet = wallet + \" /><text value=\"2\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"wallet = wallet - \" /><text value=\"1\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(wallet);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"34\" endIndex=\"35\" /><option startIndex=\"55\" endIndex=\"56\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"4\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>2</code> seguido de <code>1</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Self-assigning strings",
            "id": 71874,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Las variables establecidas en strings funcionan de la misma manera. Intenta establecer <code>nameInfo</code> a <code>nameInfo + \" John\"</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" nameInfo = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Account name:&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"nameInfo = nameInfo + \" /><text value=\"&quot; Elton&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"nameInfo = nameInfo + \" /><text value=\"&quot; John&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(nameInfo);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"75\" endIndex=\"83\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Account name: Elton John\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>nameInfo</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Assigning a value",
            "id": 72116,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>¿Cuál es el valor asignado a la variable <code>speed</code>?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" speed = \" /><text value=\"0\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /></content></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"><code>0</code></item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\"><code>speed</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>0</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Self-assigning a value",
            "id": 72117,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>¿Qué muestra este código en la consola?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"let\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" speed = \" /><text value=\"100\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"speed = speed;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(speed);\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"100\" /></content></output></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"><code>100</code></item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\"><code>5</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Asegúrese de elegir <code>100</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
